# FinTrack — session bootstrap (run before every task)

These files are **authoritative**. Do not skip or summarize from memory alone.

## 1. Always read first (every session)

- **`.github/copilot-instructions.md`** — stack, critical rules, key paths, **git workflow** (`git fetch`, branch from up-to-date `main`), `shared/project_constants.json` policy.
- **`.roo/rules/01-memory-bank-protocol.md`** — how to read/update `memory-bank/`, UMB triggers, forbidden actions.

## 2. If `memory-bank/` exists (project root)

At **session start**, read in order:

1. `memory-bank/productContext.md`
2. `memory-bank/activeContext.md`
3. `memory-bank/systemPatterns.md`

Emit one line: `[Memory Bank: Active — fintrack, focus: {≤10 words from activeContext}]`

Do not write to `memory-bank/` except on **UMB** (user says "UMB" / "update memory bank") or explicit instruction.

## 3. Git (feature work)

Before implementing features: `git fetch`, then `git checkout main && git pull`, then `git checkout -b feat/…` or `fix/…`. Do not start feature work on a stale branch without user approval.

## 4. Optional: print instructions locally

From repo root: **`python scripts/agent-instructions.py`** (or **`make agent-instructions`** if Make is installed).

## 5. `.cursorrules`

The repo `.cursorrules` file points here; this rule (`alwaysApply: true`) ensures Cursor agents load the same obligations in every chat.
